==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subgenus
<hw>Sub*ge"nus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Subgenera</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>A
subdivision of a genus, comprising one or more species which differ from
other species of the genus in some important character or characters;
<as>as, the azaleas now constitute a <ex>subgenus</ex> of
Rhododendron</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subglacial</ent>⟦br⟧
